The paper is about a deep learning model for relevance in biomedical literature search, which falls under the category of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely sub-category. The paper also uses pre-trained word embeddings, which is a common technique in natural language processing (NLP), suggesting that cs.CL (computational linguistics) is also a likely sub-category. The use of deep learning models for relevance scoring also suggests that cs.LG (machine learning) and cs.AI (artificial intelligence) are possible sub-categories. Finally, the paper specifically mentions the use of a deep convolution stage and a deep feed-forward network, indicating that cs.DL (deep learning) is also a possible sub-category.
